          <h5 class="mt-0"  >Raketh</h5>
          <p>
            Patron god of the dwarves and the forge. Raketh is responsible for the domain of fire, metal, and stone. often mostly worshiped by the very traditional dwarves, he teaches his followers that the 
            bounty underneath the earths crust belongs to them. He taught the dwarves to forge, to mine, to build. He emphasizes grandure and leaving a legacy in stone that will outlive timeitself.
            <br>
            Raketh is the god of the forge, and knowledge
            <br>
            His holy sybol is a hammer crossed with both a pickaxe and chisel
            <br>
            Raketh is often depicted as a large dwarf with a beard of fire. dark grey skin and eyes that glow like embers. his entire right arm is made of molten lava, and sculpted in the shape of a hammer.
          </p>
