            <h5 class="mt-0"  >Annam</h5>
            <p>
              God of the giants and the mountains. Annam is responsible for the domain of the earth and the sky. Annam teaches his followers to be strong, to be unyielding, to be the mountain. He teaches that the sky is the limit and that the earth is the foundation.
              Annam and his followers despise dragons, steming from dragons protecting civilizations rather than letting them grow and be stronger. Annam at one point was at war with the dragons, seeking to "libreate" the world from their tyranny.
              <br>
              Annam is responsible for the domains of the tempest, the earth and strength
              <br>
              His symbol is a fist crushing a mountain.
        
              <br>
              Annam is often depicted as a giant with a beard of clouds and eyes of lightning. his skin is an almost translucent white and his hair is the color of the sky.
            </p>
          </div>




          


